Articles.Content: He's weird, but so is Eeloo:
This has absolutely nothing to do with KSP.
But his name is Eeloo... And so is Eeloo's name.

But his name is Eeloo... And so is Eeloo's name.

It's not even spelled the same. It's a stretch at best.
E E L O O E E L O O and Eeloo was his name-oh

Eee,Loo'k over there...

(Whoosh!)

Is it a bird? Is it a plane? is it a guy who discovered "musical talent"?

Nope it's a thread, and it's in the Space Lounge, though what it's doing on these forums to begin with eludes me
Yeah, you're stretching it. His name is "elew".

Hmmm, I'm going to take your posting of the video and you seeing a connection of his name with Eeloo as a sign of your excitement and love for KSP. Perfectly understandable. After all most of us view the "Real World" in terms of KSP after a few weeks of playing -- 'that trashcan has the perfect shape for an Eve lander or I bet I could get "fill in object's name" into orbit.' It happens. Keep the faith and continue to enjoy the game.

See ya in The Black, Void
